Key Match Events: Mohamed Bayo scored the winning goal in the 90'+8' to secure Guinea's 1-0 victory over Equatorial Guinea.
Equatorial Guinea's Federico Bikoro was sent off in the 55th minute for a high-foot tackle on Bayo.
Equatorial Guinea's Iban Salvador missed a penalty in the second half.
Post-Match Reflections: Guinea ended a long sequence of losing in the AFCON knockout stages with their victory.
Equatorial Guinea's fairytale run came to an end with the loss.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Guinea will meet the winner of Sunday's later game between the Democratic Republic of Congo and Egypt in the quarterfinals.
The match was played at Alassane Ouattara Olympic Stadium in Abidjan, Ivory Coast.
Others: Guinea had brought on Naby Keita and Serhou Guirassy to inject urgency into their attack in the closing stages.
Equatorial Guinea had finished ahead of hosts Ivory Coast and Nigeria in Group A.
